4 SECTION 3. REPROGRAMMING.
5 Funds appropriated under this act shall not be reprogrammed for any other purpose and
6 notwithstanding any provision of law, all funds appropriated under this Act shall be without fiscal
7 year limitation.
8 SECTION 4. REPORTING OF EXPENDITURES.
9 Expenditure authorities of the funds allocated under Section 2 of this Act shall be responsible
10 to report all expenses to the Secretary of the Department of Finance and the Chairperson of the
11 Saipan and Northern Islands Legislative Delegation upon exhaustion of all funds allocated to each
12 respective entity. Provided further that failure to provide all expenses entities that were afforded
13 funds under this Act shall not be able to avail to any future funds appropriated by the Saipan and
14 Northern Islands Legislative Delegation.
15 SECTION 5. SEVERABILITY.
16 If any provision of this Act or the application of any such provision to any person or
17 circumstance should be held invalid by a court of competent jurisdiction, the remainder of this Act
18 or the application of its provisions to persons or circumstances other than those to which it is held
19 invalid shall not be affected thereby.
20 SECTION 6. SAVINGS CLAUSE.
21 This Act and any repealer contained herein shall not be construed as affecting any existing
